verse:
5 For the living know that they will die, but the dead know nothing;
they have no further reward, and even their name is forgotten. 6 Their love, their hate and their jealousy have long since vanished;
never again will they have a part in anything that happens under the sun.

The race is not to the swift or the battle to the strong,
nor does food come to the wise or wealth to the brilliant or favor to the learned;
but time and chance happen to them all.
